Cape Town - Firefighters continue to battle a blaze at Kylemore, outside Stellenbosch, two days after it broke out. Personnel were monitoring the perimeter of the fire, which they said was under control, while the fire within raged on.Incident commander Jaco Thuynsma said the plan was to keep the fire from spreading. He said there were no confirmed reports of injuries to people or livestock. The fire is burning at its own pace... There has been very little damage, 98% (of the) fynbos was affected and two or three informal settlements were damaged. Members of the Cape Winelands fire services, fire protection association, Stellenbosch municipality and local farmers were all collaborating to fight the blaze. Thuynsma said that firefighters were walking along the line of the fire, keeping it at bay.&nbsp;Cape Argus